# One Last Swipe — Setup Guide

## Editing profiles.json

Each profile is an object with these fields:

| Field | Description | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `name` | First name | `"Filou"` |
| `age` | Age shown on card | `25` |
| `job` | Job title (emoji friendly) | `"full time clown"` |
| `distance` | can use numbers ans letters | `"behind you "` |
| `bio` | Short tagline | `"Will fuck around"` |
| `flirt` | Completes "To flirt with me, you should:" | `"show me your tits"` |
| `photo` | Exact filename of the photo | `"lucas.jpg"` |
| `forcedMatch` | `true` = always a match on right-swipe. `false` = ~35% random chance | `true` or `false` |

## How to use it

- Photos can be JPG, PNG, WebP
- Filename matching is **case-sensitive** (`Lucas.jpg` ≠ `lucas.jpg`)
- Shuffle happens automatically on load so order in the JSON doesn't matter
